msgctxt "an4.124:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.124:0.2"
msgid "13. Bhayavagga "
msgstr "13. Fears "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: dutiyapuggalasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an4.124:0.3"
msgid "124. Dutiyanānākaraṇasutta "
msgstr "124. Difference (2nd) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an4.124:1.1"
msgid "“Cattārome, bhikkhave, puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmiṃ. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, these four people are found in the world. "

msgctxt "an4.124:1.2"
msgid "Katame cattāro? "
msgstr "What four? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.124:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, ekacco puggalo vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "Firstly, a person, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, enters and remains in the first absorption … "

msgctxt "an4.124:1.4"
msgid "So yadeva tattha hoti rūpagataṃ vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ viññāṇagataṃ, te dhamme aniccato dukkhato rogato gaṇḍato sallato aghato ābādhato parato palokato suññato anattato samanupassati. "
msgstr "They contemplate the phenomena there—included in form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness—as impermanent, as suffering, as diseased, as an abscess, as a dart, as misery, as an affliction, as alien, as falling apart, as empty, as not-self. "

msgctxt "an4.124:1.5"
msgid "So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā suddhāvāsānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the gods of the pure abodes. "

msgctxt "an4.124:1.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, upapatti asādhāraṇā puthujjanehi. "
msgstr "This rebirth is not shared with ordinary people. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "an4.124:2.1"
msgid "Puna caparaṃ, bhikkhave, idhekacco puggalo vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … pe … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … pe … catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "As the placing of the mind and keeping it connected are stilled, they enter and remain in the second absorption … third absorption … fourth absorption … "

msgctxt "an4.124:2.2"
msgid "So yadeva tattha hoti rūpagataṃ vedanāgataṃ saññāgataṃ saṅkhāragataṃ viññāṇagataṃ, te dhamme aniccato dukkhato rogato gaṇḍato sallato aghato ābādhato parato palokato suññato anattato samanupassati. "
msgstr "They contemplate the phenomena there—included in form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness—as impermanent, as suffering, as diseased, as an abscess, as a dart, as misery, as an affliction, as alien, as falling apart, as empty, as not-self. "

msgctxt "an4.124:2.3"
msgid "So kāyassa bhedā paraṃ maraṇā suddhāvāsānaṃ devānaṃ sahabyataṃ upapajjati. "
msgstr "When their body breaks up, after death, they’re reborn in the company of the gods of the pure abodes. "

msgctxt "an4.124:2.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ, bhikkhave, upapatti asādhāraṇā puthujjanehi. "
msgstr "This rebirth is not shared with ordinary people. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an4.124:2.5"
msgid "Ime kho, bhikkhave, cattāro puggalā santo saṃvijjamānā lokasmin”ti. "
msgstr "These are the four people found in the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an4.124:2.6"
msgid "Catutthaṃ. "
msgstr ""

